# Deploy Firebase rules when they change

When you **create or edit** Firebase security rules under **`catalog-cdn/`** (`firestore.rules`, `storage.rules`, or both):

1. **Deploy in the same turn** — do not leave rules only on disk. Push to project **`godive-1cff8`** from **`catalog-cdn/`**.

```bash
cd /Users/andrdugas/Desktop/GoDiveMVP/catalog-cdn
# Storage only
npx firebase-tools@latest deploy --only storage --project godive-1cff8
# Firestore only
npx firebase-tools@latest deploy --only firestore:rules --project godive-1cff8
# Both
npx firebase-tools@latest deploy --only firestore:rules,storage --project godive-1cff8
```

2. **Pick the right target(s)** — deploy only what changed (`storage` and/or `firestore:rules`). If both files changed in the same batch, deploy both.

3. **Confirm success** — report Deploy complete (or the error). Do not assume Console was updated manually.

4. **Docs** — if the rule behavior is user- or agent-facing, keep **`cursor/firebase_user_profiles.md`** in sync.

## Do not

- Ask the user to run deploy when you can run it with network / full permissions.
- Skip deploy because “they can do it later.”
- Deploy Hosting or unrelated Firebase targets unless the user asked.
